seal     : A swarm of ten thousand bees, homeless and hanging from a branch, must choose a single new home from a dozen options — and chooses, almost always, the best one. No bee compares the sites; no bee is in charge. The colony decides by a contest of dances, a swarm thinking like a brain made of bees.
